-- Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ says glitch delayed transactions
-- By Taiga Uranaka
-- Wed Apr 30, 2014 07:36AM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, April 30 (Reuters) - Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ said a system glitch on Wednesday prevented the completion of 23,000 automated money transfers for its clients.

It added that the bank had already taken measures to address the problem and it would not recur on Thursday.